  {
    "name": "Gridmaster",
    "description": "Gridmaster tasks from cache DB table 118. Test harness for the new DB-row plugin architecture - real live data that uses the same table+column model Jagex is moving L6 onto.",
    "taskJsonName": "GRID_MASTER",
    "taskSourceType": "DBROW",
    "isEnabled": false,
    "_testingNotes": "Tasks in GRID_MASTER.min.json carry dbRowId (not structId). Plugin reads via client.getDBTableField(dbRowId, colIdx, 0) instead of getStructComposition(structId).getParam(paramId). Completion tracking uses 2-step indirection: varp 4897/4898 bits hold completion of the 49 per-player grid cells (bingo_rs_7x7_row_X_col_Y dbRows 6877-6925), each of which references one of the 93 action dbRows in table 118 (this file). Static per-dbRow bit assignment doesn't exist. Placeholders 5479/5480/5481 keep plugin from crashing until someone wires up the cell-to-action runtime mapping.",
    "_columnLayout": "Column names match the cache DB column schema (action:action_name = col 0, etc). Pair columns (col 3 string/string, col 10 bool/bool, col 16 stat/int, col 23 obj/bool) are read as element 0 only via getDBTableField(row, col, 0); a multi-index loader would need a plugin change.",
